# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NOTE ON THIS SECTION:
# .gitignore only affects UNTRACKED files - it cannot stop someone from
# editing evaluate.yml itself (already tracked) or force-adding a new file
# with `git add -f`. It is NOT a security control. It just means an editor
# won't casually suggest committing a stray workflow/action file, and `git
# status` won't show one as "new file" by accident. Real enforcement is:
#   1. pull_request_target (workflow edits in the PR are ignored at run time)
#   2. the guard-protected-paths job in evaluate.yml (fails the PR check)
#   3. CODEOWNERS + "require review from Code Owners" branch protection
#   4. "Require status checks to pass" branch protection (guard job + evaluate)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.github/workflows/*
!/.github/workflows/evaluate.yml
/.github/actions/
Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml
